body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Robinson Motors. My name is David Robinson. May I have your name please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, David. My name is Elizabeth Price.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Elizabeth. Could you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's seven eight zero - four five six - two three one zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thanks. And could you also confirm your email address for me?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Elizabeth. Is there any specific car model you are interested in at the moment?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I am feeling a bit confused about the inventory. Is there a way to see what's currently available?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Certainly, we can help with that. I will guide you through our online inventory. Thank you for your time, Elizabeth.
